social_posts.post_text: Meet Hannah ♥️♥️ I shared in Tik tok and never shared here, but it definitely needed a permanent spot here too!

Hannah is 1 month old today 😭😭😭😍😍😍 and it’s been such a special month together!!

♥️She is so sweet, calm, and happy all the time. She only cries to let us know she’s hungry.
♥️She likes to eat!! She breastfeeds and bottle feeds amazing, going back and forth doesn’t bother her at all 🙏🏼
♥️She took to our schedules and is only waking up once in the night to eat, which is so amazing to me! And just like all my babies, @jefe_hauck wakes up with her in the night 🤟🏼I have to give him a shout out, thanks babe, I love you 💋
♥️She’s been such an alert baby since she was born, it’s like she doesn’t want to miss a thing 🤣😍FOMO like her mama and siblings!
♥️all the noise of our crazy house hasn’t bothered her one bit, which I was worried about 🤣
♥️ she weighs about 9 1/2 pounds and has already grown a couple inches!!!
♥️she is perfect in every way and we are all obsessed with her!! We are all fighting over who gets to hold her next (except while we’ve been sick, Jeff has gotten her all to himself 😭)
♥️we are so grateful she is here and she’s brought such a sweet, peaceful, loving spirit into our home and we feel so blessed! I especially love seeing my other kids love and mother her, it’s so sweet ♥️

They won’t stay this little forever… time truly is a thief. So here’s a reminder I needed: Let them wear the princess dress, hold them like a baby when they ask, take all the snuggles, let them express their excitement even if it feels a little crazy at times… it goes by too fast and these are the things you will miss the most. 

I had a memory pop up from 5 years ago, it was of all my medications and my calendar, I was starting the IVF process. I had so many fears and so much hope… And now I’m living my dream of being a mom 😭😭😭 to 5 beautiful children who I absolutely adore. Being a mom is hard work, and sometimes I find myself forgetting to say “yes” to the princess dresses, or putting off the chores to snuggle when they ask, or carrying them like a baby to their bed (they aren’t too big yet.) That memory from 5 years ago brought back a lot of those emotions, and I just feel overwhelmed with gratitude!!!! So I’m going to try a little harder to savor and to say “yes” to their sweet requests! 🤟🏼🙏🏼♥️ AND I’m making a goal to get back to vlogging, I miss it and I miss looking back and watching these sweet memories #motherhood

A prompting from the spirit can come in the form of a clear thought, a feeling of action, a wild idea you never thought possible, etc. and in my own life I’ve learned that promptings lead to miracles ♥️

If I had brushed off promptings I had received for years in preparation of having more children… if @nancyhauck had brushed off the prompting “carry me”… if @jefe_hauck brushed off promptings of hope in the darkest of times… we would not be holding this sweet little angel ♥️ miracles come about through promptings!

Hannah Cambria Hauck is not even two months yet but has been smiling intentionally (when she makes eye contact or recognizes a face,) since 3 weeks old, she holds her head up like she’s at least 3 months old, and she’s been so protected and we’ve done our best to keep sicknesses from our home but have found it to be inevitable with so many littles. I am SO grateful promptings were followed and she is here ♥️ every day I have a moment of wonder in how she got here and how it all came about, and it leads me to a prayer of gratitude. It all started with a prompting! Don’t underestimate a prompting 🙏🏼♥️🤟🏼 #miraclebaby #hannahcambria #hauckbabies #promptings

“Of this be sure, you do not find the happy life, you make it!” - Thomas S Monson

Such powerful words and a great reminder that your life is what you make of it. A lot of times we don’t have control over things that happen, but we can choose how we handle them. We can choose to see it as an “opportunity” to learn, grow, stretch, to choose to see it for our good! Or we can wallow… we can dwell in the hurt, in the sorrow, in the anger. BUT who is that hurting?? The answer is obvious… but I’ll say it anyway… it’s hurting YOURSELF. I’ve been in both places many times, and I’ll be there many times again.  When I choose to see the experience as something that is for my good, my eyes are opened to miracles, my heart is open to love and support, and my life is happier! Anyway, here’s a little reminder that your life is what you make it♥️ you got this!!!

They always said having kids was expensive… I misunderstood that phrase a little 🤪 #infertility after we got married I always had a couple jobs at a time, and one of them was my “fertility fund” ♥️ I would save up for the next treatment/step to having our family or getting answers. It kept my mind in a better place cause it kept me busy! Looking back, if all that had been saved I might be rich 🤣🤪😅 BUT money has never meant much to me, it’s truly a means to an end 💋 and I truly wouldn’t change a thing!!! If we didn’t do all we have done to have our family, we would be sad, lonely, and always wondering what could have been if we would have took the leap, spent the money, faced the unknown, sacrificed time and energy to save up. I’m grateful to be where we are, and if you’re in the stage before the big leap… you can do this!! Answers/your family is on the other side ♥️ it doesn’t mean it will be easy, it will hard and bumpy… but worth it! You can be broke and happy like us 🤣🤣🤣 #ivf #infertilityjourney #gesationalsurrogacy #perspective

It’s a special opportunity to welcome sweet babies to their earthly home and bless them with a name! Today’s baking segment with my mom @tonyaherbie we make Oreo balls, Easter egg style 🐣🌸💝 it’s an easy and fun recipe you can do with your kids and grandkids and it’s delish!!!! You can make all different variations by switching up the Oreo flavor, chocolate flavor/colors, etc. 

Ingredients:
🌸1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese, softened
🌸36 Oreo cookies, finely crushed
🌸16 ounces semi-sweet baking chocolate, melted 

Directions:
Step 1
Mix cream cheese and cookie crumbs until we’ll blended

Step 2
Shape onto 48 (1 inch) balls/egg shapes. Freeze 10 minutes. Dip balls in melted chocolate; place in single layer in shallow waxed paper-lined pan.

Step 3
Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.

Tips: you can make different variations for each season/holiday. Change the shape, Oreo flavor, chocolate color, etc!!!

✨Magic Coconut Bars✨
Ingredients:
- 3 packages (sleeves) of graham crackers
- 3 cubes/sticks of butter
- 2 cans of sweet and condensed milk
- shredded sweetened coconut
- chocolate chips
- sliced almonds 

Instructions:
1. On a sheet pan (11x18) unwrap 3 sticks of butter and put in the oven at 350 degrees and let melt. While waiting to melt, crush graham crackers to crumbs.
2. Take out pan from oven and add the crushed graham crackers and blend together to make a crust to fill the bottom of the pan.
3. After the crust is complete then drizzle the sweet and condensed milk all over the graham cracker crust, cover everywhere.
4. Next layer is the almonds, then the coconut, and then the chocolate chips, continue again.
5. After all layers are done then take something flat like the bottom of a glass and press the top of the bar to the pan until you see some of the milk come through. Do this to the whole pan.
6. Bake in the oven at 350 degree for 18-20 minutes, or until the almonds look toasted.

Enjoy!! These are a family favorite!!!

✨Texas Sheet Cake✨
Melt in a small sauce pan:
- 2 cubes butter
- 4 tablespoons cocoa (heaping a little)
- 1 cup water
Pour over:
- 2 cups sugar
- 2 cups flour (heaping a little)
- 1 teaspoon baking soda
- 1/2 teaspoon salt
After mixing, add 1/2 cup sour cream, buttermilk, canned milk OR coconut milk (if you make it our way!)
- 2 eggs
- 1 teaspoon vanilla
Pour batter onto a buttered and floured/greased jelly roll pan. Bake for 16-18 minutes at 375 degrees

Fudge frosting for Texas Sheet Cake
Boil:
- 1 cube butter
- 2 tablespoons cocoa (heaping a little)
- 6 tablespoons sour cream, milk, buttermilk OR coconut milk
Add: 
- 3 cups powdered sugar
- 1 teaspoon vanilla
- 1 cup chopped nuts (optional)
Frost cake while still hot or let it cool and frost for thicker frosting.

✨Homemade Waffle Recipe✨
Ingredients
* 2 cups all-purpose flour
* 2 Tablespoons granulated sugar
* 2 teaspoons baking powder
* 1 teaspoon kosher salt
* 2 large eggs
* 1 ½ cups milk
* ⅔ cup unsalted butter, melted
* 1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Instructions
* Preheat waffle griddle.
* In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. This can also be stored and made ahead for later.
* In a small bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, melted butter, and vanilla extract.
* Pour the milk mixture into the flour mixture and whisk until combined. Let sit for several minutes while iron heats up.
* Spray waffle iron with baking spray before the FIRST batch only. Ladle into preheated waffle iron and cook until golden brown. For the "DASH" brand, this will be about 3- 3 ½ minutes each.
* Serve and enjoy.

Going to Hawaii for a month has always been a dream of mine and I’ve reminded @jefe_hauck of it too often 🤣 (I call it manifesting 😜) well when the opportunity came and every box was checked we said LET’S DO IT!!! Faith was involved in this decision, I felt it was where we needed to be at this time for whatever reason. We needed the healing that comes from the ocean, simplicity, and Laie (Laie is such a special and sacred place, unlike anywhere else on earth really!) Bills, schedules, responsibilities will always be there but this stage of life is moving by fast, and money is just money ♥️ we can always work to make more 😜 AND money isn’t going with me when I’m gone, but you know what is?! These sweet memories and relationships we develop here in this life 🙏🏼🙏🏼🙏🏼

You see, we’ve spent A LOT of money to have a family. Infertility isn’t cheap. Worth every penny, but not cheap! Finances are an added struggle in infertility, and it’s so heartbreaking, and even a reason some people can’t grow their families 😭😭 I’m SO grateful to have witnessed miracles and know we’ve been blessed every step of the way 🙏🏼 the Lord is sooo good!!! Money always seemed to be there when we needed it, new opportunities to make money always presented themselves in ways we never could have imagined, and we didn’t have to get into debt to bring our babies here (blessings of tithing and faith, I have NO doubt!) So when it comes to memories we want to make, we will always save and spend the money because of the perspective infertility gave us. There’s nothing more worthwhile to spend your money on than making memories with those you love, growing and developing stronger relationship, and taking leaps of faith. I’m a dreamer, and we live off faith, and you know what… it has always worked for us and I know it always will ♥️ faith is a powerful thing. Never underestimate the power of faith! God loves you! The St George, Utah LDS temple open house will run September 15-November 11 and is free to the public’s, everyone is welcome!!!! You just reserve tickets at https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/featured/st-george-open-house?lang=eng

It’s a beautiful experience to see such a historical building and feel the love of God in this special place!

In the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints, Temples are literally houses of the Lord. They are holy places of worship where individuals make sacred covenants with God. Before they are dedicated (after dedication is when a temple recommend is required to enter,) they hold an open house to the public to come see and learn what we do in temples.

Members of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints regularly go to temples to worship. Inside these holy buildings, faithful Church members make promises with God, feel His Spirit, and come closer to Him through sacred ceremonies called ordinances. Through these ordinances, we believe that families can be sealed together forever. I love the temple and the peace and joy it brings into my life. When I need a spiritual pick me up in my life, I go to the temple. When I need more peace in my life, I go to the temple. When I am seeking answers only He can give me, I go to the temple. The temple is a physical sanctuary I can go to and feel His love. 

I LOVED getting to take my girls and answering all their questions. They wanted to go into the temple sooo bad so to be able to take them and teach them was a memory I’ll cherish forever!! I love that they wanted to get all dressed up in their “temple dresses” and they even picked out my dress too. I’m so grateful for the blessings of the temple and that I get to have them sealed to me forever!

I hope you go and see this beautiful place that so many pioneers sacrificed everything for, and to see it renovated to represent more of its pioneer heritage is amazing! #stgeorgetemple #churchofjesuschristoflatterdaysaints #templeopenhouse @churchofjesuschrist

Top tips to having a magical time in the “happiest” and busiest place on earth!!!

🎠Match!!! When else do you get to all match?! Plus it makes it easier to spot your group! Safety as well!!!

🎠A little research will go a long way!!! Come knowing the shows and attractions you want to see! Download the Disneyland app and get familiar with it!! That is also how you will want to order your food to avoid more lines at Disneyland!! Disney accounts I do research from @disneyhungry @disneylandnewstoday @disneylandfoodforever @foodatdisneyland @benchlandia seriously, knowing the things you hope to see and eat will make the world a difference for your trip!!!

🎠if you’re like me and not wanting to buy a genie+ pass (fast passes to main attractions,) then pick the rides you must ride and expect to wait BUT make the wait fun! Talk to people! Learn others stories! It makes the wait go by fast and you make a new friend!! BUT on some trips you want to get the Genie+ pass to make your trip worthwhile, with 5 littles that is not the trip so save your money!!! ✨Times I get the pass: girls trips, with adults only, with kids who can and want to ride the “big kid rides” 👏🏼 getting the pass will maximize your time there and is worth it if you’re wanting the full rides experience!

🎠it’s not a race, take it at whatever pace is ENJOYABLE to you! See how I used the word enjoyable?! Hahahaha keyword!

🎠last tip… your trip will be what you make it!!!! See the good! See the magic!!!! Yes there will be crazy crowds, inconsiderate people, sometimes cancelled fireworks, whiney kids, maybe a tantrum or two (either you or your kids 🤣) but REMEMBER that’s all part of the experience and it all is what you make it!! A BAD MOMENT DOESN’T MAKE A BAD DAY! So come with the intention to make it the best day! Ways to do that: serve others with your smile and a kind word, set out to make 5 new friends while you all are waiting in lines or for parades, take the kids to the playground areas they may just be overstimulated and need to run around, get yummy food to change the mood 🤣

So there’s a few of my best tips to ensure you have a magical day in Disneyland!!! What are some of your tips?!

When we do Disneyland with all 5 littles (ages 5 and under) the number one tip I have, is to do the things your kids want to do, it will make it so you can ENJOY THE DAY! AND go at a pace that feels enjoyable to you, you don’t have to see and do it all, and trying to will stress you out and make it hard to have a good time. 

Here’s what I do to ensure I have a perfect Disney day…I will always ask my kids what they want to do or see then WE DO IT. I tell them possible things to do and see and then listen to them and then follow by doing what they want, WHY?!?! Because I’ve learned that it makes the day way less stressful, and way more fun for everyone. When I’m trying to get them to ride a ride they think is scary, it takes the joy out of the ride for me 🤣🤣 if I’m trying to rush everyone to see something that I want, there’s always tears and unmet expectations  followed by frustration 🤣🤣 BUT when we do the things they enjoy, true child joy radiates and I love to see it!! Disneyland can be a stressful places 🤣😅 but to get that true Disney magic on every trip, try this DO THE THINGS YOUR KIDS WANT TO DO, and TAKE IT AT AN ENJOYABLE PACE ♥️ your kids won’t remember all the things they got to see or do, but they will remember how they felt in that memory, and they will remember doing the things they wanted to because it brings the feelings of having a dream fulfilled 🫶🏼👏🏼 guess what… you have full control over that… stressful and frustrating OR fun and joyful?!?! 😜 you are the magic maker 👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼
